subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia
: Pygophore rectangular to trapezoidal; genital cup well exposed dorsally; posterolateral angles of pygophore rounded, not produced; ventral rim straight or sinuate mesially; superior layer of ventral rim produced dorsally, U-shaped medially; area between ventral rim and projections of superior layer of ventral rim excavated, setose; dorsal rim concave, projected over segment X mesially, bilobate; superior process of dorsal rim present. Parameres: crown geniculate, bent laterally, broader than stem; apical process rounded to truncate, its outer surface with scale-like microsculptures; median process when present slightly developed; basal process stout, concave, with long sensilla (
Fig. 21
). Abdominal segment X convex, rectangular, with transverse grooves basally, setose apically, and posterior third with 1+1 lateral processes. Phalloteca pyriform; posterior margin slightly concave dorsally with a middle tubercle; dorsal processes of phallotheca present, digitiform, bent ventrally, not surpassing the conjunctiva. Vesica process gutter-like. Ductus seminis distalis coiled, longer than phallotheca. Conjunctiva sclerotized apically forming a black spike (
Figs 27–44
).
